<HEADLINE>
OVER 9,200 PEOPLE INDICTED UNDER ANTI-CORRUPTION OPERATION
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 10 (CNA) 03/10/07  16:41:12 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
A total of 9,245 people were indicted in 3,629 cases for bribery
or corruption during the period from July 2000 to January 2007,
with the money involved totaling NT$28.6 billion (US$867.98
million) ,  according to statistics released Saturday by the
Ministry of Justice (MOJ).
</P>
<P>
Out of the individuals indicted, 1,981 have been convicted,
according to the tallies, which are part of the MOJ's report on
the results of the ministry's operation launched in July 2000 to
crack down on bribery and corruption.
</P>
<P>
The report indicates that ever since the operation began,
district prosecutors' offices around Taiwan brought in
indictments in 3,629 cases after screening 7,677 alleged bribery
and corruption offenses.
</P>
<P>
Among the indicted, 501 were high-ranking governmental officials,
578 were local-level representatives, 4,466 were mid- or low-
ranking government employees, and 3,700 were ordinary citizens,
according to the tallies.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, there were a total of 3,881 bribery and corruption
indictments during the period between December 1993 and June
2000.
</P>
